title: Early Season Sophomore Impact Players
text: Early Season Sophomore Impact Players Ed O'Brien PaPreps.com Recruiting Analyst PA PREPS takes a look at ten sophomores who have made a big impact on their teams so far this season. Austin Dambach - Riverside - 6'3", 180Current stats: 30 catches for 538 yards and 8 TD'S through four games. Francis Duggan - North Allegheny - 6'1", 210 Current stats: 49 tackles (33 solo), 4.5 sacks through four games. Jordan Young - RB - Springside-Chestnut Hill Academy - 5'10", 180 Current stats: 67 carries for 548 yards and five touchdowns though four games. Lionel Deanes - RB - Seton-LaSalle - 5'6", 170Current stats: 47 carries for 637 yards and 8 TD'S through four games.Matt Miller - QB - DuBois - 6'2", 190Current stats: 68 of 124 passing, 1,280 yards ,12 TD'S and 5 INT'S through four games.
